1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.li Support Admin)

2
00:00:01,330 --> 00:00:03,130
You just turn around
and walk away like that.

3
00:00:03,130 --> 00:00:06,810
[Episode 6: The more veiled the truth,
the clearer the mind]

4
00:00:06,490 --> 00:00:09,220
You just turned around
and walked away like that.

5
00:00:12,610 --> 00:00:14,410
It wasn't easy for me to find you.

6
00:00:15,680 --> 00:00:17,480
I'm not letting you go this time.

7
00:00:19,480 --> 00:00:20,280
He Xiangyong!

8
00:00:41,410 --> 00:00:43,010
You've got the wrong person.

9
00:00:49,480 --> 00:00:50,910
No, I'm not.

10
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:52,370
I can feel it.

11
00:00:53,270 --> 00:00:54,670
You are He Xiangyong.

12
00:00:56,250 --> 00:00:57,450
You are He Xiangyong!

13
00:01:01,790 --> 00:01:02,890
Yeah.

14
00:01:03,790 --> 00:01:05,190
I'm as bad as him.

15
00:01:05,890 --> 00:01:07,060
As useless as him.

16
00:01:07,500 --> 00:01:09,240
We can't do anything right.

17
00:01:09,900 --> 00:01:11,330
We just drag others down

18
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:12,900
and make them clean up our mess.

19
00:01:12,900 --> 00:01:13,760
Don't say that.

20
00:01:13,940 --> 00:01:15,140
We're nothing but dead weight.

21
00:01:15,140 --> 00:01:15,990
Don't say that.

22
00:01:15,990 --> 00:01:16,860
Listen to me.

23
00:01:19,310 --> 00:01:21,340
Listen to me.

24
00:01:23,970 --> 00:01:25,140
I'm saying

25
00:01:26,750 --> 00:01:29,210
that you're the only one
who understands me.

26
00:01:30,950 --> 00:01:33,550
You gave me the best birthday gift
in the world.

27
00:01:34,160 --> 00:01:34,990
That sea turtle drawing...

28
00:01:34,990 --> 00:01:36,160
Shut up!

29
00:01:42,060 --> 00:01:44,100
You have no right to mention it.

30
00:01:45,770 --> 00:01:46,700
I...

31
00:01:49,259 --> 00:01:50,960
He's just like that drawing.

32
00:01:52,270 --> 00:01:54,000
He's already been ripped apart

33
00:01:54,300 --> 00:01:55,370
and left to rot!

34
00:01:56,910 --> 00:01:57,770
Got it?

35
00:02:04,520 --> 00:02:05,390
I'm sorry.

36
00:02:07,900 --> 00:02:10,139
I should have protected you back then.

37
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:12,660
It was my fault.

38
00:02:14,830 --> 00:02:15,720
I'm so sorry.

39
00:02:15,740 --> 00:02:16,390
Chen Haowei.

40
00:02:16,390 --> 00:02:17,070
Sorry.

41
00:02:17,250 --> 00:02:18,250
Chen Haowei.

42
00:02:20,530 --> 00:02:21,890
Don't tell me this now.

43
00:02:25,210 --> 00:02:27,840
I'm not in the mood to think about it.

44
00:02:32,210 --> 00:02:34,340
I've accepted reality a long time ago.

45
00:02:37,250 --> 00:02:38,650
The whole world hates me.

46
00:02:40,790 --> 00:02:42,090
No one likes me.

47
00:02:48,950 --> 00:02:50,320
Thanks, everyone.

48
00:03:03,180 --> 00:03:04,550
I like you.

49
00:03:05,770 --> 00:03:06,810
He Xiangyong.

50
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:36,480
Are you crazy, Chen Haowei?

51
00:03:43,030 --> 00:03:44,000
Yeah.

52
00:03:46,550 --> 00:03:47,750
I'm crazy.

53
00:03:49,420 --> 00:03:52,079
I've been crazy looking for you
all these years.

54
00:03:55,140 --> 00:03:56,780
Loving you has driven me mad.

55
00:04:01,090 --> 00:04:03,350
Do you dare to go crazy with me,
just once?

56
00:04:08,910 --> 00:04:10,010
He Xiangyong!

57
00:04:10,790 --> 00:04:12,190
Chen Haowei, let go of me!

58
00:04:12,210 --> 00:04:13,000
He Xiangyong!

59
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:14,510
Don't disappear again.

60
00:04:15,140 --> 00:04:16,540
Let go of me!

61
00:04:17,420 --> 00:04:18,220
Chen Haowei!

62
00:04:18,890 --> 00:04:20,060
Let go of me!

63
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:20,740
You...

64
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:23,520
Let go of me!

65
00:04:24,530 --> 00:04:25,790
Let go of me!

66
00:05:19,300 --> 00:05:22,020
[Wishing Upon the Shooting Stars]

67
00:05:23,080 --> 00:05:24,320
Where is He Xiangyong?

68
00:05:24,320 --> 00:05:25,250
Here we are.

69
00:05:26,300 --> 00:05:28,400
Let's have more drinks!

70
00:05:31,430 --> 00:05:33,490
Here we are. You should get some rest.

71
00:05:33,590 --> 00:05:34,730
I'm heading home.

72
00:05:35,110 --> 00:05:37,550
No way. You're not going anywhere.

73
00:05:39,870 --> 00:05:41,470
Are you a koala or something?

74
00:05:41,670 --> 00:05:42,600
I'm...

75
00:05:43,090 --> 00:05:44,060
I'm...

76
00:05:44,610 --> 00:05:45,970
a big wolf.

77
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:48,610
Well,

78
00:05:49,409 --> 00:05:51,050
then I guess that makes me
Little Red Riding Hood.

79
00:05:51,050 --> 00:05:52,350
No, you're not.

80
00:05:53,380 --> 00:05:55,840
You're a gift
that fell from a shooting star.

81
00:05:56,620 --> 00:05:58,950
The gift that happened
to land right on me.

82
00:06:02,490 --> 00:06:04,690
So you're really not letting me go, huh?

83
00:06:04,830 --> 00:06:06,390
Don't you like me?

84
00:06:06,860 --> 00:06:09,060
If you like me, then why would you leave?

85
00:06:13,630 --> 00:06:15,200
It's so warm.

86
00:06:15,870 --> 00:06:17,310
I'm so happy.

87
00:06:18,510 --> 00:06:19,840
I wish we could be together like this

88
00:06:19,840 --> 00:06:21,840
every day.

89
00:06:25,750 --> 00:06:27,080
You won't regret it?

90
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:29,920
I don't know.

91
00:06:41,060 --> 00:06:42,860
I'm afraid I might lose control.

92
00:06:58,159 --> 00:06:59,970
This way, you won't.

93
00:07:02,940 --> 00:07:04,610
I can't take it anymore.

94
00:07:04,630 --> 00:07:06,190
Can't take what?

95
00:07:12,870 --> 00:07:14,140
It tickles.

96
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:34,570
Wait.

97
00:08:36,809 --> 00:08:38,010
What are you doing?

98
00:08:39,620 --> 00:08:41,159
You kissed me like that.

99
00:08:41,850 --> 00:08:44,049
And now you're asking me what I'm doing?

100
00:08:45,020 --> 00:08:46,790
No.

101
00:08:50,660 --> 00:08:51,830
Next time.

102
00:08:59,970 --> 00:09:00,880
Li Wanzhe.

103
00:09:00,910 --> 00:09:03,280
Dudu, stop it, okay?

104
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:14,070
He really can't hold his liquor.

105
00:09:43,970 --> 00:09:45,400
Please.

106
00:09:46,230 --> 00:09:47,750
Chen Haowei.

107
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:03,460
How did we get back to the guesthouse
yesterday?

108
00:10:17,150 --> 00:10:18,220
Right.

109
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:22,000
Did I bring you back?

110
00:10:24,890 --> 00:10:26,400
What are you talking about?

111
00:10:26,400 --> 00:10:28,330
It was more like I brought you back.

112
00:10:29,570 --> 00:10:30,980
Whatever.

113
00:10:33,810 --> 00:10:35,780
I'm thirsty.

114
00:10:35,810 --> 00:10:38,340
Rock, paper, scissors.
Loser gets the water.

115
00:10:39,120 --> 00:10:41,550
Rock, paper, scissors.

116
00:10:41,570 --> 00:10:44,080
I've prepared fish soup and tea for you.

117
00:10:44,610 --> 00:10:46,140
They're for your hangover.

118
00:10:46,570 --> 00:10:49,010
Drink them all.

119
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:51,210
The pot calls the kettle black.

120
00:10:57,920 --> 00:10:59,020
Mr. He.

121
00:11:00,550 --> 00:11:01,310
We...

122
00:11:01,660 --> 00:11:04,120
didn't cause any trouble yesterday,
did we?

123
00:11:05,910 --> 00:11:07,610
Why don't you take a guess?

124
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:08,870
Pot.

125
00:11:14,740 --> 00:11:15,700
I'll show you.

126
00:11:15,700 --> 00:11:17,000
You're going further and further out.

127
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:17,850
Watch out!

128
00:11:19,580 --> 00:11:20,950
What's that?

129
00:11:20,970 --> 00:11:21,800
What is that?

130
00:11:21,940 --> 00:11:23,210
What do you see?

131
00:11:23,460 --> 00:11:25,320
Why are there two people up ahead?

132
00:11:25,810 --> 00:11:26,500
Who are they?

133
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:27,930
Why are they lying here?

134
00:11:29,780 --> 00:11:30,890
No.

135
00:11:31,650 --> 00:11:32,620
This way.

136
00:11:34,040 --> 00:11:34,940
Don't throw up.

137
00:11:37,730 --> 00:11:38,390
Oh, come on.

138
00:11:38,390 --> 00:11:40,250
Why are you throwing up like that?

139
00:11:40,360 --> 00:11:41,430
My clothes!

140
00:11:41,430 --> 00:11:42,630
They are ruined.

141
00:11:43,110 --> 00:11:45,680
You need to take them
to the laundry for me.

142
00:11:45,700 --> 00:11:46,770
Take it easy.

143
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:52,370
Anyway, that's what happened.

144
00:11:52,970 --> 00:11:55,380
And you said you would take care of him.

145
00:11:57,850 --> 00:11:59,250
Mr. He, I'm sorry.

146
00:11:59,870 --> 00:12:00,940
We won't

147
00:12:01,010 --> 00:12:02,470
drink that much next time.

148
00:12:04,770 --> 00:12:05,520
Forget it.

149
00:12:06,790 --> 00:12:07,460
I guess

150
00:12:07,460 --> 00:12:09,590
everyone's been feeling down lately.

151
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:11,430
You guys finish the fish porridge.

152
00:12:11,430 --> 00:12:12,690
Then get ready to work.

153
00:12:12,980 --> 00:12:14,250
I'm going fishing.

154
00:12:21,430 --> 00:12:22,690
Thanks, Mr. He.

155
00:12:49,190 --> 00:12:49,880
Well,

156
00:12:50,430 --> 00:12:51,830
last night...

157
00:12:53,730 --> 00:12:55,100
Last night?

158
00:12:56,820 --> 00:12:57,450
Well...

159
00:12:57,840 --> 00:12:58,510
You...

160
00:13:00,640 --> 00:13:01,240
Me?

161
00:13:03,060 --> 00:13:03,840
We...

162
00:13:05,380 --> 00:13:06,170
We?

163
00:13:09,250 --> 00:13:10,160
Nothing.

164
00:13:10,450 --> 00:13:11,390
I'm just saying

165
00:13:11,390 --> 00:13:12,920
we were lucky last night.

166
00:13:12,940 --> 00:13:14,800
We could've been run over by a car.

167
00:13:17,450 --> 00:13:18,710
Speaking of which,

168
00:13:19,700 --> 00:13:20,900
my body feels like

169
00:13:20,920 --> 00:13:22,820
it's been hit by a train.

170
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:24,360
It's aching everywhere.

171
00:13:59,300 --> 00:14:01,770
Angela, you're totally fine.

172
00:14:02,190 --> 00:14:02,890
Really?

173
00:14:04,210 --> 00:14:05,310
But I just feel like...

174
00:14:05,310 --> 00:14:06,170
You know what?

175
00:14:09,230 --> 00:14:10,490
Something's off here.

176
00:14:10,710 --> 00:14:11,780
Can you check it again for me?

177
00:14:11,780 --> 00:14:12,410
No need.

178
00:14:12,410 --> 00:14:13,710
I've already heard it. It's fine.

179
00:14:13,710 --> 00:14:14,820
Look at you.

180
00:14:14,820 --> 00:14:15,750
You look great.

181
00:14:17,180 --> 00:14:18,050
Okay.

182
00:14:18,420 --> 00:14:19,750
I think I look great too.

183
00:14:21,100 --> 00:14:22,160
Let me borrow that.

184
00:14:22,930 --> 00:14:24,570
Let me see if you're okay.

185
00:14:24,590 --> 00:14:26,650
What could possibly be wrong with me?

186
00:14:30,050 --> 00:14:31,850
Alright, you look great too.

187
00:14:34,970 --> 00:14:36,670
He doesn't look great.

188
00:14:36,690 --> 00:14:39,190
What's wrong with him?

189
00:14:39,220 --> 00:14:40,690
He...

190
00:14:40,710 --> 00:14:42,840
What could possibly be wrong with him?

191
00:14:45,130 --> 00:14:47,260
Then why is he selling the guesthouse?

192
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:22,550
I'm sorry

193
00:15:25,350 --> 00:15:27,610
that I didn't take good care of this home.

194
00:15:35,020 --> 00:15:35,970
Where's the tape?

195
00:15:35,970 --> 00:15:37,880
I told you to find the tape.

196
00:15:39,190 --> 00:15:40,350
I couldn't find it.

197
00:15:44,180 --> 00:15:45,840
Then go through

198
00:15:47,040 --> 00:15:48,440
the maps and photo frames

199
00:15:48,440 --> 00:15:49,580
in the guesthouse.

200
00:15:49,780 --> 00:15:51,510
Anything that can be recycled,
sort it all out

201
00:15:51,510 --> 00:15:53,010
and find a place to take it.

202
00:15:54,150 --> 00:15:54,950
Wait.

203
00:15:55,400 --> 00:15:56,220
We haven't signed the contract yet.

204
00:15:56,220 --> 00:15:57,620
Why are you in such a hurry?

205
00:15:57,620 --> 00:15:59,780
We have to do it sooner or later.

206
00:15:59,800 --> 00:16:00,940
Hurry up. Sort it out.

207
00:16:00,940 --> 00:16:01,600
Get it done.

208
00:16:03,850 --> 00:16:05,310
What about the guestbook?

209
00:16:05,720 --> 00:16:07,320
Are you throwing it away too?

210
00:16:11,550 --> 00:16:13,550
Xiangyong was the one who bought it.

211
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:17,360
I'll wait for him to come back and decide.

212
00:16:18,860 --> 00:16:19,830
He.

213
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:21,490
He.

214
00:16:22,760 --> 00:16:25,800
Your VIPs are here.

215
00:16:26,990 --> 00:16:27,990
He.

216
00:16:29,980 --> 00:16:32,110
You don't have to sell the guesthouse.

217
00:16:32,850 --> 00:16:34,490
Look.

218
00:16:35,640 --> 00:16:38,390
Village Chief Wang alone
donated twenty thousand.

219
00:16:38,390 --> 00:16:41,140
And the guy I ran into outside,

220
00:16:41,170 --> 00:16:42,630
De from the grocery store,

221
00:16:42,630 --> 00:16:45,030
gave us all his earnings from yesterday.

222
00:16:45,480 --> 00:16:46,480
And Auntie Jiao,

223
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:49,100
who doesn't know how to use the ATM,

224
00:16:49,130 --> 00:16:50,430
went back home

225
00:16:50,460 --> 00:16:52,200
and brought out her dowry.

226
00:16:52,220 --> 00:16:53,520
This is from Jinfa.

227
00:16:53,550 --> 00:16:54,740
And this is from Chunhua.

228
00:16:54,740 --> 00:16:55,680
They all donated.

229
00:16:55,680 --> 00:16:56,920
Hua, where's yours?

230
00:16:57,060 --> 00:16:58,460
Mine's already in there.

231
00:17:00,020 --> 00:17:02,020
This is a token of our appreciation.

232
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:04,240
Thank you.

233
00:17:04,839 --> 00:17:06,569
But this isn't enough.

234
00:17:06,599 --> 00:17:07,730
Take it back.

235
00:17:17,329 --> 00:17:18,670
Now add mine.

236
00:17:18,700 --> 00:17:19,670
Five million.

237
00:17:19,700 --> 00:17:20,900
There you go.

238
00:17:26,310 --> 00:17:27,780
You can't do that.

239
00:17:28,560 --> 00:17:30,760
This is everyone's hard-earned money.

240
00:17:31,110 --> 00:17:32,170
Especially yours.

241
00:17:32,850 --> 00:17:34,880
You worked so hard to raise Wanzhe.

242
00:17:34,880 --> 00:17:36,850
This is the pension
that you've been saving for years.

243
00:17:36,850 --> 00:17:37,950
Keep it. Enjoy your retirement.

244
00:17:37,950 --> 00:17:39,010
Don't give it to me.

245
00:17:39,580 --> 00:17:41,320
Don't be silly!

246
00:17:41,850 --> 00:17:43,210
You and your wife used to

247
00:17:43,240 --> 00:17:44,900
help me take care of Wanzhe every day,

248
00:17:44,900 --> 00:17:45,600
right?

249
00:17:45,630 --> 00:17:46,960
And listen.

250
00:17:46,990 --> 00:17:48,300
Here, this money.

251
00:17:48,300 --> 00:17:49,300
What?

252
00:17:49,300 --> 00:17:51,480
I'm not giving it to you as a gift.

253
00:17:51,580 --> 00:17:52,840
I'm lending it to you.

254
00:17:53,570 --> 00:17:55,400
Okay, let me make this clear.

255
00:17:56,250 --> 00:17:57,890
We're writing an IOU.

256
00:17:57,910 --> 00:17:59,610
And we're charging interest.

257
00:17:59,630 --> 00:18:00,630
Hey, Xiaoyou.

258
00:18:00,930 --> 00:18:02,400
Go get me the ink pad.

259
00:18:02,430 --> 00:18:03,260
Here.

260
00:18:03,310 --> 00:18:03,910
Right.

261
00:18:03,940 --> 00:18:05,510
He, stop being so stubborn.

262
00:18:06,420 --> 00:18:07,510
You know we have so many memories

263
00:18:07,510 --> 00:18:08,920
in this guesthouse.

264
00:18:10,040 --> 00:18:10,990
For Xingpu Island,

265
00:18:10,990 --> 00:18:12,190
and for Xiangyong,

266
00:18:12,220 --> 00:18:13,220
just take it.

267
00:18:14,720 --> 00:18:15,450
Take it.

268
00:18:15,590 --> 00:18:16,650
Alright. Alright.

269
00:18:20,620 --> 00:18:21,660
What now?

270
00:18:23,450 --> 00:18:25,020
You'd rather sell the guesthouse

271
00:18:25,020 --> 00:18:26,450
to a stranger

272
00:18:26,470 --> 00:18:28,190
than owe me money?

273
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:30,670
Are you looking down on me?

274
00:18:30,670 --> 00:18:31,640
-Is that it?
-No, that's not what I meant.

275
00:18:31,640 --> 00:18:32,770
No.

276
00:18:37,410 --> 00:18:38,650
I owe you so much.

277
00:18:38,650 --> 00:18:40,780
I don't know how I'll ever pay you back.

278
00:18:42,840 --> 00:18:44,070
How?

279
00:18:44,100 --> 00:18:46,560
Work harder and make more money,
that's how.

280
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:48,440
If you don't pay me back,

281
00:18:48,460 --> 00:18:52,030
I'll tear down this house.

282
00:18:52,060 --> 00:18:53,510
Then I'll bring my dog here
to pee every day.

283
00:18:53,510 --> 00:18:55,710
And I'll throw away all the flowers

284
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:57,090
that your wife brought!

285
00:18:57,100 --> 00:18:58,400
-No!
-No!

286
00:19:02,660 --> 00:19:03,860
I'll help pay it back.

287
00:19:04,850 --> 00:19:06,380
It's none of your business.

288
00:19:07,210 --> 00:19:08,210
I'm your son...

289
00:19:09,740 --> 00:19:10,840
Your son's friend.

290
00:19:10,870 --> 00:19:12,130
And I'm your employee.

291
00:19:12,410 --> 00:19:13,610
I want to help too.

292
00:19:16,580 --> 00:19:17,420
Awesome!

293
00:19:18,290 --> 00:19:18,990
Awesome!

294
00:19:19,940 --> 00:19:20,930
You're a lucky man.

295
00:19:20,930 --> 00:19:22,800
Your employee is so loyal.

296
00:19:25,130 --> 00:19:26,790
Okay, everything's fine now.

297
00:19:26,880 --> 00:19:27,910
Let's go fishing.

298
00:19:28,560 --> 00:19:29,460
No, you go ahead.

299
00:19:29,460 --> 00:19:31,060
I already went this morning.

300
00:19:31,270 --> 00:19:32,300
I'll go throw up.

301
00:19:32,730 --> 00:19:33,800
I told you not to drink too much.

302
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:34,840
Now you want to throw up, huh?

303
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:36,100
You drank way too much.

304
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:40,340
You guys are so mushy.
That's what makes me want to throw up.

305
00:19:40,340 --> 00:19:42,280
You guys take care of that money, okay?

306
00:19:42,280 --> 00:19:43,510
I'll go open up the shop.

307
00:19:43,510 --> 00:19:43,880
Bye.

308
00:19:43,880 --> 00:19:45,150
Which way are you trying to go?

309
00:19:45,150 --> 00:19:46,050
Move!

310
00:19:46,050 --> 00:19:47,680
God, you're so annoying!

311
00:20:12,350 --> 00:20:13,450
One more.

312
00:20:14,310 --> 00:20:15,540
Come on.

313
00:20:20,570 --> 00:20:22,100
What's up? You're so quiet.

314
00:20:22,280 --> 00:20:23,650
You're here fishing with me.

315
00:20:23,650 --> 00:20:25,980
So I guess
you have something on your mind.

316
00:20:29,190 --> 00:20:30,060
Uncle Hua,

317
00:20:30,590 --> 00:20:32,590
why are you floating these paper boats?

318
00:20:32,590 --> 00:20:34,560
I'm saying hello to the dolphins.

319
00:20:36,060 --> 00:20:36,800
Dolphins?

320
00:20:38,670 --> 00:20:41,400
When I was a resident at the main island,

321
00:20:42,700 --> 00:20:44,160
there was a little patient

322
00:20:45,470 --> 00:20:48,530
who had been in and out of the hospital
since childhood.

323
00:20:49,480 --> 00:20:51,480
He really envied the sea creatures.

324
00:20:52,560 --> 00:20:55,760
Because he thought they could swim
wherever they wanted.

325
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:59,540
He even wished
that he could be a little dolphin.

326
00:21:00,190 --> 00:21:03,190
That way, he wouldn't need
any more shots or medicine.

327
00:21:03,790 --> 00:21:05,330
So I joked with him,

328
00:21:05,700 --> 00:21:06,290
"Okay.

329
00:21:07,220 --> 00:21:09,350
Then I'll take a boat to come find you."

330
00:21:21,260 --> 00:21:22,760
So these paper boats

331
00:21:23,400 --> 00:21:25,800
hold that kind of memory for you,
Uncle Hua.

332
00:21:30,120 --> 00:21:31,990
I wasn't mature enough back then.

333
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:36,040
I wasn't strong enough
to fight for what I believed was right.

334
00:21:36,720 --> 00:21:39,250
So I caused damage
that could never be undone.

335
00:21:42,830 --> 00:21:45,230
And that's why
I've stayed on Xingpu Island

336
00:21:46,070 --> 00:21:47,300
all this time.

337
00:21:55,640 --> 00:21:57,240
What? Are you disappointed?

338
00:21:58,580 --> 00:21:59,610
I never had the kind of ambition

339
00:21:59,610 --> 00:22:01,810
that Schweitzer had, to save humanity.

340
00:22:02,480 --> 00:22:04,380
My story is more like

341
00:22:05,850 --> 00:22:07,620
a coward running away.

342
00:22:14,330 --> 00:22:16,060
Everyone has their own memories.

343
00:22:16,060 --> 00:22:18,000
I'm not in a position to judge.

344
00:22:20,830 --> 00:22:21,700
But

345
00:22:23,770 --> 00:22:25,710
I feel like I just saw my old self.

346
00:22:29,780 --> 00:22:31,220
If I'd

347
00:22:32,610 --> 00:22:33,410
had more courage

348
00:22:33,410 --> 00:22:35,940
to protect the person
who mattered most to me,

349
00:22:37,120 --> 00:22:37,820
maybe things wouldn't be

350
00:22:37,820 --> 00:22:39,390
so complicated now.

351
00:22:42,890 --> 00:22:43,960
What's the matter?

352
00:22:44,590 --> 00:22:45,990
Run into some trouble?

353
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:49,430
Anyway,

354
00:22:49,720 --> 00:22:52,250
the first part of the dream was fuzzy.

355
00:22:52,930 --> 00:22:54,300
I only remember,

356
00:22:54,300 --> 00:22:56,300
in the end, the handsome guy

357
00:22:56,300 --> 00:22:57,900
kissed that loser.

358
00:22:57,900 --> 00:22:59,010
And then I woke up.

359
00:23:00,760 --> 00:23:02,830
So you kissed Chen Haowei last night?

360
00:23:02,860 --> 00:23:03,990
I didn't say that.

361
00:23:04,010 --> 00:23:05,050
Don't deny it.

362
00:23:05,080 --> 00:23:06,300
We've known each other for so long.

363
00:23:06,300 --> 00:23:08,300
Just tell me who made the first move.

364
00:23:09,780 --> 00:23:10,880
It was me.

365
00:23:12,450 --> 00:23:13,770
How's Xiaoyou's reaction?

366
00:23:13,770 --> 00:23:18,600
I think I pushed him away.

367
00:23:20,360 --> 00:23:21,330
I forgot.

368
00:23:21,330 --> 00:23:23,730
I told you I only remember
the kissing part.

369
00:23:25,700 --> 00:23:27,700
Do you think he was just drunk

370
00:23:27,730 --> 00:23:29,660
and trying to take advantage of me?

371
00:23:30,290 --> 00:23:31,630
No way.

372
00:23:31,650 --> 00:23:34,050
Is Chen Haowei
really that kind of monster?

373
00:23:34,640 --> 00:23:35,840
You're right.

374
00:23:35,840 --> 00:23:37,440
He's not that kind of person.

375
00:23:39,310 --> 00:23:42,510
He was probably drunk
and just confessed how he loved you.

376
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:44,150
Are you talking about me

377
00:23:44,150 --> 00:23:45,150
or Zhong Xiaoyou?

378
00:23:45,150 --> 00:23:47,410
I admit that I have feelings for Xiaoyou.

379
00:23:48,370 --> 00:23:49,730
I think I like him.

380
00:23:53,510 --> 00:23:55,550
If you like him, just tell him.

381
00:23:55,570 --> 00:23:57,170
What's there to worry about?

382
00:23:58,270 --> 00:23:58,970
No.

383
00:23:59,570 --> 00:24:00,700
I like Xiaoyou

384
00:24:01,090 --> 00:24:03,220
because I thought he was He Xiangyong.

385
00:24:05,760 --> 00:24:07,820
The name I kept calling last night

386
00:24:09,090 --> 00:24:10,190
was He Xiangyong.

387
00:24:11,980 --> 00:24:14,450
So he doesn't remember kissing you?

388
00:24:14,890 --> 00:24:16,290
Nope.

389
00:24:16,420 --> 00:24:17,580
From how he acted this morning,

390
00:24:17,580 --> 00:24:19,070
it was like he forgot everything.

391
00:24:19,070 --> 00:24:20,680
But if he really likes Xiaoyou,

392
00:24:20,680 --> 00:24:22,110
like you said,

393
00:24:22,140 --> 00:24:24,260
then how could he just forget about it?

394
00:24:24,260 --> 00:24:26,800
Or maybe he mistook Xiaoyou for you,

395
00:24:26,860 --> 00:24:28,790
so he pretended nothing happened.

396
00:24:29,170 --> 00:24:30,240
What a jerk.

397
00:24:31,500 --> 00:24:32,370
That's why I can't

398
00:24:32,370 --> 00:24:34,120
confess to Xiaoyou.

399
00:24:36,610 --> 00:24:38,180
Because I know

400
00:24:38,650 --> 00:24:40,350
they are not the same person.

401
00:24:40,930 --> 00:24:42,550
I may have confused them before,

402
00:24:42,550 --> 00:24:43,350
but

403
00:24:46,070 --> 00:24:48,000
the person on my mind is Xiangyong.

404
00:24:49,420 --> 00:24:51,760
I can't treat Xiaoyou as his replacement.

405
00:24:52,090 --> 00:24:52,950
Well, if that's the case,

406
00:24:52,950 --> 00:24:55,320
I think you should stick with it.

407
00:24:55,620 --> 00:24:58,080
Don't start
the wrong kind of relationship.

408
00:24:58,590 --> 00:24:59,690
Otherwise,

409
00:25:00,160 --> 00:25:02,260
Xiaoyou is going to get really hurt.

410
00:25:03,430 --> 00:25:04,430
That's not right.

411
00:25:04,530 --> 00:25:06,370
Whether it's Zhong Xiaoyou
or He Xiangyong,

412
00:25:06,370 --> 00:25:07,730
you are still you.

413
00:25:07,730 --> 00:25:09,190
It's just like snow cone and shaved ice.

414
00:25:09,190 --> 00:25:11,120
Same thing, just different names.

415
00:25:13,520 --> 00:25:15,990
That's some crazy logic you've got.

416
00:25:18,310 --> 00:25:20,240
But it seems to make sense.

417
00:25:26,670 --> 00:25:27,970
Now that you mention it,

418
00:25:27,970 --> 00:25:30,370
Chen Haowei has always
been devoted to you.

419
00:25:30,410 --> 00:25:32,020
It's so romantic.

420
00:25:33,630 --> 00:25:35,160
Are you going to accept him?

421
00:25:36,010 --> 00:25:37,250
Accept what?

422
00:25:38,420 --> 00:25:40,290
And as who?

423
00:25:40,320 --> 00:25:41,520
As me?

424
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:43,530
Or as Zhong Xiaoyou?

425
00:25:44,820 --> 00:25:46,020
Besides,

426
00:25:46,210 --> 00:25:48,110
I have nothing left to tear apart.

427
00:25:49,650 --> 00:25:52,250
Dude, can you please
talk like a normal person?

428
00:25:58,820 --> 00:26:00,860
But look.

429
00:26:00,880 --> 00:26:02,660
Our wishes just came true like that.

430
00:26:02,660 --> 00:26:05,890
Don't you feel it's a bit unsettling?

431
00:26:07,420 --> 00:26:08,660
It's like

432
00:26:08,680 --> 00:26:10,880
if you find a million bucks on the street

433
00:26:10,880 --> 00:26:11,880
and bring it home,

434
00:26:12,970 --> 00:26:14,430
would you really be happy?

435
00:26:21,690 --> 00:26:22,790
Li Wanzhe!

436
00:26:25,470 --> 00:26:28,000
Hama-chan,
you're not going out to sea today?

437
00:26:28,080 --> 00:26:29,280
I quit my job!

438
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:32,460
I'll be working here from now on!

439
00:26:32,460 --> 00:26:33,920
Let's work well together!

440
00:27:05,740 --> 00:27:06,810
Tell me.

441
00:27:06,840 --> 00:27:08,240
Why did you quit?

442
00:27:08,260 --> 00:27:09,660
Did something happen?

443
00:27:09,790 --> 00:27:11,320
Or did Bingzhong bully you?

444
00:27:12,480 --> 00:27:14,180
Your face is so funny.

445
00:27:14,810 --> 00:27:16,470
You look just like Bingzhong.

446
00:27:16,840 --> 00:27:18,210
Hamaguchi Soukai.

447
00:27:18,230 --> 00:27:20,330
I'm trying to be serious with you.

448
00:27:24,500 --> 00:27:25,670
Don't worry.

449
00:27:26,700 --> 00:27:28,310
I'm fine.

450
00:27:28,340 --> 00:27:29,940
No one bullied me.

451
00:27:31,910 --> 00:27:32,710
I quit my job

452
00:27:33,570 --> 00:27:34,540
because of you.

453
00:27:35,550 --> 00:27:36,220
Me?

454
00:27:36,850 --> 00:27:37,280
Yes.

455
00:27:37,770 --> 00:27:38,810
Last night, you told me

456
00:27:38,810 --> 00:27:41,740
that you wanted to stay with me
and have fun every day.

457
00:27:41,900 --> 00:27:43,330
So I quit my job.

458
00:27:44,010 --> 00:27:46,010
That way, I can be with you every day.

459
00:27:46,590 --> 00:27:47,650
When did I say that?

460
00:27:48,900 --> 00:27:49,700
You forgot?

461
00:27:52,380 --> 00:27:53,780
Let me remind you.

462
00:27:57,400 --> 00:27:59,530
You said it while holding me like this.

463
00:28:01,640 --> 00:28:02,910
I'm so happy.

464
00:28:03,440 --> 00:28:04,480
It's so warm.

465
00:28:05,310 --> 00:28:06,550
I wish we could be together like this

466
00:28:06,550 --> 00:28:08,050
every day.

467
00:28:10,170 --> 00:28:11,330
Well?

468
00:28:11,350 --> 00:28:12,960
Does it feel familiar?

469
00:28:14,620 --> 00:28:15,690
People talk nonsense when they're drunk.

470
00:28:15,690 --> 00:28:17,490
How could you take it seriously?

471
00:28:18,220 --> 00:28:19,520
I told you.

472
00:28:20,710 --> 00:28:22,040
I'll do everything I can

473
00:28:22,220 --> 00:28:23,490
when it comes to you.

474
00:28:26,330 --> 00:28:27,030
But

475
00:28:27,800 --> 00:28:28,970
you said

476
00:28:29,470 --> 00:28:31,040
being a sailor was your dream.

477
00:28:31,040 --> 00:28:33,240
You said you wanted to travel the world.

478
00:28:44,430 --> 00:28:45,460
From now on,

479
00:28:46,770 --> 00:28:48,040
you are my dream.

480
00:28:48,830 --> 00:28:50,600
You are my whole world.

481
00:28:52,120 --> 00:28:54,720
Boss, I'm heading to work now.

482
00:29:29,600 --> 00:29:32,200
What do you need to write?
I can write it for you.

483
00:29:33,130 --> 00:29:34,210
Okay, you write the words.

484
00:29:34,210 --> 00:29:35,410
No drawing, alright?

485
00:29:35,740 --> 00:29:38,470
I'm saving that for Xiangyong
when he comes back.

486
00:29:46,070 --> 00:29:47,630
He made such a mess

487
00:29:47,650 --> 00:29:48,990
and just disappeared.

488
00:29:49,920 --> 00:29:50,920
Aren't you angry?

489
00:29:51,070 --> 00:29:53,270
Why are you still doing all this for him?

490
00:29:54,400 --> 00:29:55,330
I am angry.

491
00:29:56,060 --> 00:29:56,890
I'm angry at myself

492
00:29:56,890 --> 00:29:59,620
for not teaching him
how to box when he was little.

493
00:29:59,740 --> 00:30:01,070
Because of that,

494
00:30:02,100 --> 00:30:04,900
he can only hold it in
when he's wronged.

495
00:30:08,690 --> 00:30:10,150
Are you worried about him?

496
00:30:10,820 --> 00:30:13,350
Aren't you afraid
that he might not come back?

497
00:30:20,380 --> 00:30:22,050
Of course I am.

498
00:30:25,580 --> 00:30:27,450
But he has his reasons.

499
00:30:28,550 --> 00:30:30,610
Anyway, his home and his dad are here.

500
00:30:31,130 --> 00:30:33,400
He can come back whenever he wants.

501
00:30:37,970 --> 00:30:38,940
If he finds out

502
00:30:39,890 --> 00:30:41,490
that you almost

503
00:30:41,830 --> 00:30:43,430
sold the guesthouse for him,

504
00:30:43,980 --> 00:30:47,380
he'll definitely come drink with me
for three days straight.

505
00:30:48,180 --> 00:30:50,820
And he'll cry,
saying how immature he's been.

506
00:30:52,730 --> 00:30:53,730
This is heavy.

507
00:30:53,760 --> 00:30:55,760
He can't even drink.

508
00:30:57,200 --> 00:30:58,440
You don't know?

509
00:31:02,130 --> 00:31:04,990
His way of curing a hangover
is climbing a mountain.

510
00:31:06,250 --> 00:31:08,920
Once he reaches the top,
he can see the ocean

511
00:31:10,070 --> 00:31:11,430
and Xingpu Island.

512
00:31:21,370 --> 00:31:23,810
When did he start drinking?

513
00:31:25,630 --> 00:31:27,090
After he started working.

514
00:31:32,890 --> 00:31:34,460
That brat.

515
00:31:36,260 --> 00:31:38,320
He'll go out and drink with others,

516
00:31:40,190 --> 00:31:43,200
but he won't even have one with me
at home.

517
00:31:45,800 --> 00:31:46,930
He just doesn't want you

518
00:31:46,930 --> 00:31:48,900
to see his weak side.

519
00:31:50,650 --> 00:31:51,920
When he's drunk,

520
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:55,730
he talks too much,
acts like a kid, and cries a lot.

521
00:31:56,230 --> 00:31:57,630
I bet you don't like that.

522
00:31:58,530 --> 00:31:59,630
It's nothing.

523
00:32:00,030 --> 00:32:01,970
He takes after me.

524
00:32:04,460 --> 00:32:06,390
In his eyes,

525
00:32:06,410 --> 00:32:08,780
I'm just a bad-tempered father

526
00:32:08,810 --> 00:32:11,450
who's not worth sharing his thoughts with.

527
00:32:13,530 --> 00:32:14,990
It's not like that.

528
00:32:16,480 --> 00:32:18,010
He knows

529
00:32:18,030 --> 00:32:20,360
that everything you do
is for his own good.

530
00:32:21,020 --> 00:32:22,030
He just

531
00:32:22,560 --> 00:32:24,290
doesn't know how to express it.

532
00:32:28,440 --> 00:32:30,700
Then I was right to keep that chalkboard.

533
00:32:31,700 --> 00:32:34,670
Xiangyong has always been a sensitive kid.

534
00:32:35,520 --> 00:32:36,460
His drawings

535
00:32:37,400 --> 00:32:39,860
are probably his way
of showing how he feels.

536
00:32:45,210 --> 00:32:46,090
By the way,

537
00:32:46,580 --> 00:32:48,250
tell him

538
00:32:48,360 --> 00:32:51,260
that his dad only hates
one type of drinker.

539
00:32:51,670 --> 00:32:54,810
The type who makes a scene
when they're drunk.

540
00:32:57,000 --> 00:32:57,860
Isn't that you?

541
00:32:59,060 --> 00:32:59,990
Shut up.

542
00:33:03,280 --> 00:33:04,010
When he comes back,

543
00:33:04,010 --> 00:33:06,610
why don't you just
ask him for a drink yourself?

544
00:33:20,180 --> 00:33:21,740
I'll be the chef today.

545
00:33:22,270 --> 00:33:23,960
I'll make you some drinking snacks

546
00:33:23,960 --> 00:33:25,330
and your favorite
garlic shrimp vermicelli.

547
00:33:25,330 --> 00:33:26,070
You know how?

548
00:33:26,630 --> 00:33:27,430
Of course I do.

549
00:33:27,570 --> 00:33:29,700
That's Xiangyong's mother's special dish.

550
00:33:29,700 --> 00:33:30,960
You know how to cook it?

551
00:33:31,400 --> 00:33:32,610
He taught me.

552
00:33:33,060 --> 00:33:33,960
You can't cook it.

553
00:33:33,960 --> 00:33:34,810
But you're lucky.

554
00:33:34,810 --> 00:33:35,420
Because I can.

555
00:33:35,420 --> 00:33:36,280
I'll cook for you.

556
00:33:36,280 --> 00:33:37,740
I know how to do it. Don't worry.

557
00:33:37,740 --> 00:33:39,070
I'm confident, okay?

558
00:33:39,990 --> 00:33:41,350
Young man,

559
00:33:42,680 --> 00:33:43,350
I'm starting to wonder

560
00:33:43,350 --> 00:33:45,410
about your relationship with my son.

561
00:33:46,210 --> 00:33:47,270
We're just friends.

562
00:33:47,270 --> 00:33:48,910
The kind that tell each other everything.

563
00:33:48,910 --> 00:33:49,880
No.

564
00:33:49,910 --> 00:33:51,540
He even taught you that?

565
00:33:51,560 --> 00:33:52,820
You know how to cook it?

566
00:33:55,820 --> 00:33:57,110
Are you sure you know how to cook it?

567
00:33:57,110 --> 00:33:58,320
I'm sure.

568
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:00,200
Is the oil hot enough?

569
00:34:01,030 --> 00:34:02,030
Just wait for it.

570
00:34:03,030 --> 00:34:03,890
Wait for it.

571
00:34:03,920 --> 00:34:04,960
It's almost there.

572
00:34:04,960 --> 00:34:07,200
The shrimp

573
00:34:08,489 --> 00:34:09,620
and the vermicelli.

574
00:34:11,580 --> 00:34:12,710
Don't let the oil get too hot,

575
00:34:12,710 --> 00:34:14,350
or the garlic will burn, you know?

576
00:34:14,350 --> 00:34:16,320
I know. Just fry it a little.

577
00:34:17,020 --> 00:34:17,850
Don't fry it too long.

578
00:34:17,850 --> 00:34:19,090
Hurry up and add the chili.

579
00:34:19,090 --> 00:34:19,719
Hurry.

580
00:34:19,719 --> 00:34:20,870
It's fine.

581
00:34:20,889 --> 00:34:22,449
This is how I've always done it, okay?

582
00:34:22,449 --> 00:34:24,290
That's not gonna work.

583
00:34:24,310 --> 00:34:26,110
Trust me. It's fine.

584
00:34:27,760 --> 00:34:28,360
I can't watch this.

585
00:34:28,360 --> 00:34:29,530
Here, move over.

586
00:34:29,530 --> 00:34:30,130
Please.

587
00:34:30,130 --> 00:34:31,199
Go stand aside.

588
00:34:31,630 --> 00:34:34,170
I told you. I'm cooking today.

589
00:34:34,170 --> 00:34:35,739
Go make the sauce for me, okay?

590
00:34:35,739 --> 00:34:37,440
Please. Thank you.

591
00:34:55,920 --> 00:34:57,790
Not bad.

592
00:34:58,360 --> 00:34:59,560
You need to throw that out quickly.

593
00:34:59,560 --> 00:35:01,090
Otherwise,

594
00:35:01,090 --> 00:35:02,560
add some water.

595
00:35:10,350 --> 00:35:11,800
[Hope you're doing well.
This is a really wonderful place. Haowei]

596
00:35:25,520 --> 00:35:26,650
Chen Haowei.

597
00:35:28,650 --> 00:35:29,390
It's almost done.

598
00:35:29,390 --> 00:35:30,690
Time to eat.

599
00:35:32,980 --> 00:35:34,040
What are you doing?

600
00:35:44,640 --> 00:35:46,770
If you happen to run into He Xiangyong,

601
00:35:48,300 --> 00:35:50,000
give this to him for me.

602
00:35:57,530 --> 00:35:58,790
I'll go help Mr. He now.

603
00:36:22,420 --> 00:36:24,350
[He Xiangyong]

604
00:36:52,670 --> 00:36:59,480
[Epilogue]

605
00:37:01,910 --> 00:37:03,020
Chen Haowei.

606
00:37:04,550 --> 00:37:05,690
What are you doing?

607
00:37:05,890 --> 00:37:07,290
I'm waiting for someone.

608
00:37:07,430 --> 00:37:08,690
Are you waiting for me?

609
00:37:09,990 --> 00:37:10,960
Just kidding.

610
00:37:11,250 --> 00:37:13,050
I saw you looking at the drawing.

611
00:37:13,690 --> 00:37:14,730
Yes.

612
00:37:14,730 --> 00:37:15,830
Can I see it?

613
00:37:19,870 --> 00:37:20,730
Let me take a look.

614
00:37:20,730 --> 00:37:21,400
Okay.

615
00:37:22,640 --> 00:37:24,170
A sea turtle!

616
00:37:24,170 --> 00:37:26,070
Yeah. I really like sea turtles.

617
00:37:28,690 --> 00:37:30,180
Did He Xiangyong draw this?

618
00:37:30,180 --> 00:37:31,980
Yeah. Why?

619
00:37:34,450 --> 00:37:35,510
Don't you think

620
00:37:35,510 --> 00:37:38,260
his childlike touch is kind of ugly?

621
00:37:38,410 --> 00:37:40,340
What's that?

622
00:37:40,870 --> 00:37:42,370
No wonder you were laughing.

623
00:37:42,370 --> 00:37:44,230
This is what you were laughing at.

624
00:37:45,130 --> 00:37:45,970
Well, yeah.

625
00:37:46,000 --> 00:37:47,250
I think it's worth laughing at.

626
00:37:47,250 --> 00:37:49,350
Yeah, I think so too.

627
00:37:51,000 --> 00:37:52,470
Let me tell you.

628
00:37:52,500 --> 00:37:53,720
He Xiangyong is a really,

629
00:37:53,720 --> 00:37:55,060
really strange person.

630
00:37:55,090 --> 00:37:56,960
No one in our class likes him.

631
00:37:56,980 --> 00:37:58,440
But I think you're really kind.

632
00:37:58,440 --> 00:38:00,610
You still spend time being his friend

633
00:38:00,630 --> 00:38:02,530
and help him with his homework and stuff.

634
00:38:02,530 --> 00:38:04,360
Yeah, just helping a classmate.

635
00:38:04,930 --> 00:38:06,560
So you think he needs help too?

636
00:38:06,560 --> 00:38:07,650
Then we are very similar.

637
00:38:07,650 --> 00:38:08,920
We both help people

638
00:38:08,940 --> 00:38:10,640
who seem like they need it.

639
00:38:11,870 --> 00:38:14,370
Can you do me a favor?

640
00:38:15,150 --> 00:38:15,920
What is it?

641
00:38:15,950 --> 00:38:17,260
I want to borrow it.

642
00:38:17,600 --> 00:38:20,330
Just let me borrow it.
I'll give it back next week.

643
00:38:21,140 --> 00:38:22,670
Aren't you in the art class?

644
00:38:22,690 --> 00:38:24,490
You can draw it yourself, right?

645
00:38:30,300 --> 00:38:32,300
Class is starting. I gotta go.

646
00:39:10,840 --> 00:39:12,440
Chen Haowei says he's tired.

647
00:39:16,550 --> 00:39:17,550
You know Chen Haowei

648
00:39:17,550 --> 00:39:19,190
is a popular student in the school.

649
00:39:19,190 --> 00:39:20,220
He has a lot of friends.

650
00:39:20,220 --> 00:39:21,560
And everyone likes him.

651
00:39:21,940 --> 00:39:23,440
So any event,

652
00:39:23,470 --> 00:39:24,140
any club...

653
00:39:24,160 --> 00:39:25,620
What are you trying to say?

654
00:39:29,050 --> 00:39:30,410
I'm just saying

655
00:39:30,920 --> 00:39:32,510
Chen Haowei's grades have dropped.

656
00:39:32,510 --> 00:39:34,370
And he's been dozing off in class.

657
00:39:34,430 --> 00:39:35,760
You think it's my fault?

658
00:39:37,040 --> 00:39:38,240
I didn't say that.

659
00:39:38,650 --> 00:39:40,780
Why do you have to think the worst of me?

660
00:39:40,960 --> 00:39:42,030
Based on the fact

661
00:39:42,050 --> 00:39:43,970
that we're both good friends
of Chen Haowei,

662
00:39:43,970 --> 00:39:45,210
I want to offer a suggestion

663
00:39:45,210 --> 00:39:47,420
that would help both you and him.

664
00:39:49,330 --> 00:39:51,930
Haven't you considered
going to a cram school?

665
00:39:54,500 --> 00:39:55,460
No need.

666
00:39:56,310 --> 00:39:58,310
I won't bother Chen Haowei anymore.

667
00:39:59,690 --> 00:40:01,220
Why are you being like that?

668
00:40:02,830 --> 00:40:03,950
I'm just saying

669
00:40:03,980 --> 00:40:06,270
that I was also influenced by Chen Haowei.

670
00:40:06,270 --> 00:40:08,130
So I want to work with him

671
00:40:08,130 --> 00:40:10,440
to help classmates like you
who are falling behind.

672
00:40:10,440 --> 00:40:11,270
Let's work harder

673
00:40:11,270 --> 00:40:14,000
and get better together.
Wouldn't that be great?

674
00:40:15,870 --> 00:40:17,070
No need.

675
00:40:17,640 --> 00:40:18,980
I'm tired.

676
00:40:18,980 --> 00:40:20,550
I don't want to work harder.

677
00:40:26,230 --> 00:40:27,120
He Xiangyong.

678
00:40:29,290 --> 00:40:30,360
If there's anything

679
00:40:30,360 --> 00:40:31,320
you need help with,

680
00:40:31,320 --> 00:40:32,580
you can always tell me.

681
00:40:33,170 --> 00:40:34,100
Really.

682
00:40:42,690 --> 00:40:43,960
Just let me know.

683
00:41:26,220 --> 00:41:32,320
[Next Episode]

684
00:41:27,150 --> 00:41:28,280
If you want to go see him off,

685
00:41:28,280 --> 00:41:30,080
you can still make it to the pier.

686
00:41:31,320 --> 00:41:33,050
The person I can't let go of
is He Xiangyong.

687
00:41:33,050 --> 00:41:35,690
The person I've always loved
is also He Xiangyong.

688
00:41:35,690 --> 00:41:38,820
You don't need to turn yourself
into He Xiangyong for me.

689
00:41:39,180 --> 00:41:39,940
Li Wanzhe.

690
00:41:39,960 --> 00:41:41,130
Are you hungry?

691
00:41:41,160 --> 00:41:43,300
You've been working hard all day.

692
00:41:43,320 --> 00:41:44,920
Let me make you some late-night snacks.
